(9, '<p>A particle is moving with a uniform speed in a circular orbit of radius \\({\\text{R}}\\) in a central force <strong>inversely proportional</strong> to the \\({n^{th}}\\) power of \\({\\text{R}}\\) . If the period of rotation of the particle is \\({\\text{T}}\\) , then:</p>', '<p>Given \\(F = \\cfrac{K}{{{r^n}}}\\) </p><p>Using definition of Centripetal force</p><p> \\(\\cfrac{{m{V^2}}}{r} = \\cfrac{K}{{{r^n}}}\\) </p><p> \\({V^2} \\propto \\cfrac{K}{{{r^{n - 1}}}}\\) </p><p> \\(V \\propto \\cfrac{1}{{{r^{\\cfrac{{n - 1}}{2}}}}}\\) </p><p> \\(T = \\cfrac{{2\\pi r}}{V} \\propto \\cfrac{r}{V}\\) </p><p> \\(T \\propto \\cfrac{r}{{\\cfrac{1}{{{r^{\\cfrac{{n - 1}}{2}}}}}}}\\) </p><p> \\(T \\propto {R^{\\cfrac{{n + 1}}{2}}}\\) </p>', '<p> \\(T \\propto {R^{n/2}}\\) </p>', '<p> \\(T \\propto {R^{3/2}}\\) for any \\(n\\) </p>', '<p> \\(T \\propto {R^{\\cfrac{n}{2} + 1}}\\) </p>', '<p> \\(T \\propto {R^{\\cfrac{{n + 1}}{2}}}\\) </p>', 0, 0, 0, 1),
