(11, '<p>In an a.c circuit, the instantaneous e.m.f. and current are given by</p><p> \\(e = 100\\sin 30t\\) </p><p> \\(r = 20\\sin \\left( {30t - \\cfrac{\\pi }{4}} \\right)\\) </p><p>In one cycle of a.c., the average power consumed by the circuit and the wattles current are, respectively:</p>', '<p> \\(e = 100\\sin 30t\\) </p><p> \\(r = 20\\sin \\left( {30t - \\cfrac{\\pi }{4}} \\right)\\) </p><p>Average power \\( = {V_{rms}}{I_{rms}}\\cos \\phi \\) </p><p> \\( = \\cfrac{{100}}{{\\sqrt 2 }} \\times \\cfrac{{20}}{{\\sqrt 2 }} \\times \\cfrac{1}{{\\sqrt 2 }}\\) </p><p> \\( = \\cfrac{{1000}}{{\\sqrt 2 }}\\) Watt</p><p><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"images/2020022515520450.png\" max-width=\"190\" max-height=\"172\" /></p><p>Wattless Current = \\({{\\text{I}}_{{\\text{rms}}}}\\sin \\theta \\) </p><p> \\( = \\cfrac{{{{\\text{I}}_{\\text{o}}}}}{{\\sqrt 2 }}\\sin 45\\) </p><p> \\( = \\cfrac{{20}}{{\\sqrt 2 }} \\cdot \\cfrac{1}{{\\sqrt 2 }} = 10{\\text{A}}\\) </p>', '<p>50, 0</p>', '<p>50, 10</p>', '<p> \\(\\cfrac{{1000}}{{\\sqrt 2 }}, 10\\) </p>', '<p> \\(\\cfrac{{50}}{{\\sqrt 2 }}, 10\\) </p>', 0, 0, 1, 0),
