(25, '<p>On interchanging the resistances, the balance point of a meter bridge shifts to the left by 10 cm. The resistance of their series combination is \\(1\\, \\, k\\Omega \\) . How much was the resistance on the left slot before interchanging the resistances?</p>', '<p><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"images/2020022515531696.png\" max-width=\"247\" max-height=\"141\" /></p><p> \\(\\cfrac{a}{b} = \\cfrac{l}{{100 - l}}\\) </p><p> \\(a + b = 1000\\) </p><p> \\(\\cfrac{b}{a} = \\cfrac{{l - 10}}{{110 - l}}\\) </p><p> \\(\\cfrac{{100 - l}}{l} = \\cfrac{{l - 10}}{{110 - l}}\\) </p><p> \\({l^2} - 10l = 11000 + {l^2}\\) </p><p> \\( - 100l = 110l\\) </p><p> \\(200l = 11000\\) </p><p> \\(l = \\cfrac{{110}}{2} = 55\\) </p><p> \\(\\cfrac{{55}}{{45}} = \\cfrac{a}{b}\\) </p><p> \\( \\Rightarrow \\) \\(a = 550\\Omega \\) \\(b = 450\\Omega \\) </p>', '<p> \\(910\\, \\, \\Omega \\) </p>', '<p> \\(990\\, \\, \\Omega \\) </p>', '<p> \\(505\\, \\, \\Omega \\) </p>', '<p> \\(550\\, \\, \\Omega \\) </p>', 0, 0, 0, 1),
(26, '<p>In a potentiometer experiment, it is found that no current passes through the galvanometer when the terminals of the cell are connected across 52 cm of the potentiometer wire. If the cell is shunted by a<br />resistance of \\(5\\Omega \\) , balance is found when the cell is connected across 40 cm of the wire. Find the internal resistance of the cell.</p>', '<p>Without shunting condiction:</p><p><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"images/2020022515532237.png\" max-width=\"212\" max-height=\"138\" /></p><p> \\({E_s} = 52 \\times x\\) &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.(i)</p><p>when balanced</p><p>Where, \\(x = \\) potential gradient of wire.</p><p>with shunting condition</p><p><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"images/2020022515532225.png\" max-width=\"162\" max-height=\"153\" /></p><p>On balancing</p><p> \\({E_s} - \\cfrac{E}{{(r + R)}}r = 40 \\times x\\) &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;(ii)</p><p>On solving:</p><p> \\(\\cfrac{{(i)}}{{(ii)}} \\Rightarrow \\cfrac{1}{{1 - \\cfrac{r}{{r + R}}}} = \\cfrac{{52}}{{40}}\\) </p><p> \\(r = 1.5\\, \\, \\Omega \\) </p>', '<p> \\(2.5\\, \\, \\Omega \\) </p>', '<p> \\(1\\, \\, \\Omega \\) </p>', '<p> \\(1.5\\, \\, \\Omega \\) </p>', '<p> \\(2\\, \\, \\Omega \\) </p>', 0, 0, 1, 0),
(27, '<p>If the series limits frequency of the Lyman series is \\({V_L}, \\) then the series limits frequency of the Pfund series is:</p>', '<p>Series limit frequency of the Lyman series is given by \\({V_2} = RC{Z^2}\\left( {\\cfrac{1}{{{1^2}}} - \\cfrac{1}{{{\\infty ^2}}}} \\right)\\) </p><p> \\({V^2} = RC{Z^2}\\) </p><p>Series limit frequency of the Pfund series</p><p> \\({V_p} = RC{Z^2}\\left( {\\cfrac{1}{{{5^2}}} - \\cfrac{1}{{{\\infty ^2}}}} \\right)\\) </p><p> \\({V_p} = \\cfrac{{{V_L}}}{{25}}\\) </p>', '<p> \\(\\cfrac{{{V_L}}}{{25}}\\) </p>', '<p> \\(25{V_L}\\) </p>', '<p> \\(16{V_L}\\) </p>', '<p> \\(\\cfrac{{{V_L}}}{{16}}\\) </p>', 1, 0, 0, 0),
(28, '<p>The angular width of the central maximum in a single slit diffraction pattern is \\({60^\\circ }\\) . The width of the slit is 1 \\(\\mu m\\) . The slit is illuminated by monochromatic plane waves. If another slit of same width is made near it, Youngs fringes can be observed on a screen placed at a distance 50 cm from the slits. If the observed fringe width is 1 cm, what is slit separation distance?<br />(i.e. distance between the centres of each slit.)</p>', '<p>In diffraction</p><p> \\(d\\sin {30^\\circ } = \\lambda \\) </p><p> \\(\\lambda = \\cfrac{d}{2}\\) </p><p><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"images/2020022515532970.png\" max-width=\"163\" max-height=\"118\" /></p><p>Youngs fringe width [d-separation between two slits</p><p> \\(\\beta = \\cfrac{{\\lambda \\times D}}{{{d^\\prime }}}\\) </p><p> \\({10^{ - 2}} = \\cfrac{d}{2} \\times \\cfrac{{50 \\times {{10}^{ - 2}}}}{{{d^\\prime }}}\\) </p><p> \\({10^{ - 2}} = \\cfrac{{{{10}^{ - 6}} \\times 50 \\times {{10}^{ - 2}}}}{{2 \\times {d^\\prime }}}\\) </p><p> \\({d^\\prime } = 25\\mu m\\) </p>', '<p> \\(100\\mu m\\) </p>', '<p> \\(25\\mu m\\) </p>', '<p> \\(50\\mu m\\) </p>', '<p> \\(75\\mu m\\) </p>', 0, 1, 0, 0),
(29, '<p>A particle is moving in a circular path of radius a under the action of an attractive potential \\(U = - \\cfrac{k}{{2{r^2}}}.\\) Its total energy is:</p>', '<p> \\(U = - \\cfrac{K}{{2{r^2}}}\\) </p><p> \\(F = - \\cfrac{{dU}}{{dr}} = \\cfrac{{2K}}{{2{r^3}}} = \\cfrac{K}{{{r^3}}}\\) </p><p> \\(\\cfrac{{m{v^2}}}{r} = \\cfrac{K}{{{r^3}}}\\) </p><p> \\({v^2} = \\cfrac{K}{{m{r^2}}}\\) </p><p> \\(\\cfrac{1}{2}m{v^2} = \\cfrac{K}{{2{r^2}}}\\) </p><p> \\(E = \\cfrac{K}{{2{r^2}}} - \\cfrac{K}{{2{r^2}}} = 0\\) </p>', '<p> \\( - \\cfrac{3}{2}\\cfrac{k}{{{a^2}}}\\) </p>', '<p> \\( - \\cfrac{k}{{4{a^2}}}\\) </p>', '<p> \\(\\cfrac{k}{{2{a^2}}}\\) </p>', '<p>Zero</p>', 0, 0, 0, 1),
(30, '<p>A silver atom in a solid oscillates in simple harmonic motion in some direction with a frequency of \\({10^{12}}/\\) sec. What is the force constant of the bonds connecting one atom with the other? (Mole wt. of silver \\( = 108\\) and Avagadro number \\( = 6.02 \\times {10^{23}}\\) )</p>', '<p> \\(v = {10^{12}}{s^{ - 1}}\\) </p><p> \\(w = \\sqrt {\\cfrac{k}{m}} \\) ( \\({\\text{K}}\\) is Force constant)</p><p> \\(T = 2\\pi \\sqrt {\\cfrac{m}{k}} \\) </p><p> \\(v = \\cfrac{1}{{2\\pi }}\\sqrt {\\cfrac{k}{m}} \\) </p><p> \\(v = \\cfrac{1}{{2\\pi }}\\sqrt {\\cfrac{{K \\times 6.02 \\times {{10}^{23}}}}{{108 \\times {{10}^{ - 3}}}}} \\) </p><p> \\(K = \\cfrac{{4{\\pi ^2} \\times {{10}^{24}} \\times 108 \\times {{10}^{ - 3}}}}{{6.02 \\times {{10}^{23}}}}\\) </p><p> \\( \\approx 7.1\\, \\, {\\text{N/m}}\\) </p>', '<p> \\(5.5\\, {\\text{N/m}}\\) </p>', '<p> \\(6.4\\, {\\text{N/m}}\\) </p>', '<p> \\(7.1\\, {\\text{N/m}}\\) </p>', '<p> \\(2.2\\, {\\text{N/m}}\\) </p>', 0, 0, 1, 0);

